\frac{1}{2}
\lim_{x\to 0}\frac{\sqrt{x+1}-1}{x} = \frac{1}{2}
\require{cancel}
\sqrt{x+1} + 1
(\sqrt a - b) \cdot (\sqrt a + b) = (\sqrt a)^2 - b^2 = a - b^2
\dfrac {\sqrt{x+1} - 1}{x} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{x+1} + 1}{\sqrt{x+1} + 1} = \dfrac {(x + 1) - 1 }{x(\sqrt{x+1} + 1)} \dfrac {\cancel{x}}{\cancel{x}(\sqrt{x+1} + 1)} = \dfrac 1{\sqrt{x + 1} + 1}
\lim_{x \to 0} \dfrac 1{\sqrt{x + 1} + 1}
